&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B. Sairam.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ministry of Coal appointed B. Sairam as the new Chairman-cum-Managing Director of Coal India Limited.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B. Sairam took charge as CMD of Coal India Limited, replacing Sanoj Kumar Jha, who was holding additional charge.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Before this appointment, he served as the CMD of Northern Coalfields Limited, a wholly owned subsidiary of Coal India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coal India Limited functions as a central public sector enterprise under the Ministry of Coal.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CIL is the world&amp;rsquo;s largest coal mining company and plays a critical role in ensuring India&amp;rsquo;s energy security.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Coal India Limited (CIL)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;World&amp;rsquo;s largest coal-producing company by volume.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Operates under the administrative control of the Ministry of Coal.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Plays a pivotal role in meeting India&amp;rsquo;s thermal power and industrial fuel requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Northern Coalfields Limited (NCL)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A wholly owned subsidiary of Coal India Limited.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Major coal producer supplying to power plants in northern India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;CMD Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The CMD is responsible for overall strategic direction, operational efficiency, and policy implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The position is crucial for managing India&amp;rsquo;s coal production and supply chain stability.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;$135.46 billion&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Diaspora remittances hit new record at $135.46 bn in FY25.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;276&quot; data-start=&quot;169&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;276&quot; data-start=&quot;171&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong data-end=&quot;194&quot; data-start=&quot;175&quot;&gt;Indian diaspora&lt;/strong&gt; sent home &lt;strong data-end=&quot;224&quot; data-start=&quot;205&quot;&gt;$135.46 billion&lt;/strong&gt; in remittances in FY25 &amp;mdash; the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;275&quot; data-start=&quot;254&quot;&gt;highest on record&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;381&quot; data-start=&quot;277&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;381&quot; data-start=&quot;279&quot;&gt;This marks a &lt;strong data-end=&quot;308&quot; data-start=&quot;292&quot;&gt;14% increase&lt;/strong&gt; over the previous year, according to &lt;strong data-end=&quot;375&quot; data-start=&quot;346&quot;&gt;RBI&amp;rsquo;s Balance of Payments&lt;/strong&gt; data.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;475&quot; data-start=&quot;382&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;475&quot; data-start=&quot;384&quot;&gt;India has been the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;424&quot; data-start=&quot;403&quot;&gt;largest recipient&lt;/strong&gt; of &lt;strong data-end=&quot;452&quot; data-start=&quot;428&quot;&gt;diaspora remittances&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong data-end=&quot;474&quot; data-start=&quot;453&quot;&gt;for over a decade&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;589&quot; data-start=&quot;476&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;589&quot; data-start=&quot;478&quot;&gt;Inflows have &lt;strong data-end=&quot;512&quot; data-start=&quot;491&quot;&gt;more than doubled&lt;/strong&gt; in 8 years &amp;mdash; from &lt;strong data-end=&quot;557&quot; data-start=&quot;531&quot;&gt;$61 billion in 2016&amp;ndash;17&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong data-end=&quot;588&quot; data-start=&quot;561&quot;&gt;$135.46 billion in FY25&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;711&quot; data-start=&quot;590&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;711&quot; data-start=&quot;592&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;630&quot; data-start=&quot;592&quot;&gt;Remittances accounted for over 10%&lt;/strong&gt; of India&amp;rsquo;s &lt;strong data-end=&quot;675&quot; data-start=&quot;642&quot;&gt;gross current account inflows&lt;/strong&gt; (totaling &lt;strong data-end=&quot;701&quot; data-start=&quot;686&quot;&gt;$1 trillion&lt;/strong&gt; in FY25).&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;801&quot; data-start=&quot;712&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;801&quot; data-start=&quot;714&quot;&gt;Major sources of remittances: &lt;strong data-end=&quot;761&quot; data-start=&quot;744&quot;&gt;United States&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong data-end=&quot;781&quot; data-start=&quot;763&quot;&gt;United Kingdom&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;800&quot; data-start=&quot;787&quot;&gt;Singapore&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;904&quot; data-start=&quot;802&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;904&quot; data-start=&quot;804&quot;&gt;These inflows &lt;strong data-end=&quot;855&quot; data-start=&quot;818&quot;&gt;help offset India&amp;rsquo;s trade deficit&lt;/strong&gt; and are a &lt;strong data-end=&quot;903&quot; data-start=&quot;866&quot;&gt;stable source of external funding&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tango.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FIFA unveiled three mascots for the 2026 World Cup: Clutch the Bald Eagle (USA), Maple the Moose (Canada), and Zayu the Jaguar (Mexico).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clutch represents the United States and symbolizes courage, curiosity, and inclusivity, playing the role of a midfielder.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maple represents Canada, embodying cultural diversity and natural beauty, acting as the goalkeeper.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Zayu represents Mexico, symbolizing heritage, agility, and creativity, playing as a striker.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tango is not associated with the 2026 FIFA World Cup mascots; the official mascots are Clutch, Maple, and Zayu.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Multi-Mascot Introduction&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This is the first time FIFA has introduced multiple mascots for a senior men&amp;rsquo;s World Cup, reflecting the multi-nation hosting format and expanded tournament structure.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;2026 World Cup Hosts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The tournament is co-hosted by the United States, Canada, and Mexico, with 48 teams competing in 104 matches.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Mascot Roles&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Each mascot has a football position and personality traits to engage fans and symbolize the cultural and sporting spirit of their respective countries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Event Highlights&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The opening match is on June 11, 2026, at Estadio Azteca, Mexico City, and the final will feature the first-ever halftime show at MetLife Stadium, New Jersey, on July 19, 2026.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Delhi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OpenAI has announced that it will open its first India office in New Delhi later in 2025, marking a significant step in its global expansion strategy.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India is ChatGPT&amp;rsquo;s second-largest user base after the United States, with students forming the largest user group globally.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India is among the top five global developer markets on the OpenAI platform, making it a strategic hub.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The New Delhi office will support India&amp;rsquo;s AI ecosystem by engaging with government, academia, startups, and enterprises.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OpenAI will host its first Education Summit in August 2025 and Developer Day later in 2025 in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;IndiaAI Mission&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A national initiative to promote trusted, inclusive AI development in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aligned with OpenAI&amp;rsquo;s vision to democratize AI tools across education, governance, agriculture, and enterprises.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Sam Altman&amp;rsquo;s Vision&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;CEO of OpenAI emphasized India&amp;rsquo;s tech talent, developer culture, and proactive government support.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Described the New Delhi office as &amp;ldquo;an important first step&amp;rdquo; in building AI for India and with India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Broader Benefits&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Expected to foster AI talent, generate jobs, and strengthen India&amp;rsquo;s global role in AI workforce.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Will expand educational and professional opportunities with AI-powered tools.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Numaligarh Refinery Limited (NRL).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Numaligarh Refinery Ltd (NRL) has been granted Navratna status, marking a major milestone for Assam&amp;rsquo;s oil and gas sector.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NRL has been upgraded to Navratna status.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The announcement was hailed by Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Union Petroleum Minister Hardeep Singh Puri praised NRL&amp;rsquo;s performance and growth projects.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Status grants higher financial autonomy and investment flexibility for expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Numaligarh Refinery Limited (NRL)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Located in Assam; a key PSU in the oil &amp;amp; gas sector.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Undergoing major expansion under NREP from 3 to 9 MMTPA.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Promoter: Oil India Ltd; Partner: Engineers India Ltd, Assam Govt.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Navratna Status&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Granted to high-performing PSUs with operational and financial excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Allows greater investment power without government approval.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Sits below Maharatna &amp;amp; above Miniratna category.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recent Developments&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;2G bamboo-based bioethanol plant commissioned (India&amp;rsquo;s first commercial scale).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Boosts green energy transition and supports bamboo farmers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Importance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Strengthens energy security &amp;amp; industrial growth in Northeast India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Expected to accelerate upcoming refinery and petrochemical projects.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hansalpur, Ahmedabad.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Prime Minister inaugurated two major milestones at the Suzuki Motor plant in Hansalpur, Ahmedabad &amp;mdash; the global launch of Suzuki&amp;rsquo;s first strategic Battery Electric Vehicle &amp;ldquo;e VITARA&amp;rdquo; and the start of hybrid battery electrode production in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The &amp;ldquo;e VITARA&amp;rdquo; will be manufactured in India and exported to over 100 countries, including Europe and Japan.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;With this, India becomes Suzuki&amp;rsquo;s global manufacturing hub for electric vehicles.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Prime Minister also inaugurated local production of hybrid battery electrodes at TDS Lithium-Ion Battery plant in Gujarat.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This initiative ensures that more than 80% of the battery value will now be manufactured within India, boosting clean energy innovation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;e VITARA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Suzuki&amp;rsquo;s first global strategic Battery Electric Vehicle (BEV).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A flagship example of &amp;ldquo;Make in India&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Aatmanirbhar Bharat.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;TDS Lithium-Ion Battery Plant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A joint venture of Toshiba, Denso, and Suzuki in Gujarat.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Commenced local production of hybrid battery electrodes in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Boosts India&amp;rsquo;s domestic battery ecosystem and reduces import dependence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Significance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Reinforces India&amp;rsquo;s role as a global hub for green mobility.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Strengthens India&amp;rsquo;s clean energy innovation and EV supply chain.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lok Sabha Speaker Om Birla.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lok Sabha Speaker Om Birla will lead the Indian Parliamentary Delegation to the 68th Commonwealth Parliamentary Conference (CPC) to be held in Bridgetown, Barbados, from October 5 to 12, 2025.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Om Birla chaired an inter-ministerial briefing at Parliament House ahead of the conference.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The delegation will also include Rajya Sabha Deputy Chairman Harivansh and presiding officers of state and UT legislatures.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Birla will address the General Assembly on the theme &amp;ldquo;The Commonwealth: A Global Partner.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The conference will feature seven thematic workshops and a youth roundtable on challenges like cyber-bullying and gang violence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Commonwealth Parliamentary Conference (CPC)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;One of the largest annual gatherings of parliamentarians from 180 CPA branches.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Acts as a platform for dialogue on democracy, governance, and global cooperation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Rajya Sabha Deputy Chairman Harivansh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Part of the Indian delegation but not leading it.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;President Droupadi Murmu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Head of State of India, not involved in leading parliamentary delegations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S/2025 U1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;NASA Discovers 29th Satellite of Uranus, Named S/2025 U1.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;184&quot; data-start=&quot;88&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;184&quot; data-start=&quot;90&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;98&quot; data-start=&quot;90&quot;&gt;NASA&lt;/strong&gt; announced the discovery of the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;148&quot; data-start=&quot;130&quot;&gt;29th satellite&lt;/strong&gt; of &lt;strong data-end=&quot;162&quot; data-start=&quot;152&quot;&gt;Uranus&lt;/strong&gt;, named &lt;strong data-end=&quot;183&quot; data-start=&quot;170&quot;&gt;S/2025 U1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;297&quot; data-start=&quot;185&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;297&quot; data-start=&quot;187&quot;&gt;The moon was identified by a team led by the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;271&quot; data-start=&quot;232&quot;&gt;Southwest Research Institute (SwRI)&lt;/strong&gt; on &lt;strong data-end=&quot;296&quot; data-start=&quot;275&quot;&gt;2nd February 2025&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;423&quot; data-start=&quot;298&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;423&quot; data-start=&quot;300&quot;&gt;The moon has an estimated &lt;strong data-end=&quot;355&quot; data-start=&quot;326&quot;&gt;diameter of 10 kilometres&lt;/strong&gt; and orbits &lt;strong data-end=&quot;377&quot; data-start=&quot;367&quot;&gt;Uranus&lt;/strong&gt; at a distance of about &lt;strong data-end=&quot;422&quot; data-start=&quot;401&quot;&gt;56,000 kilometres&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;551&quot; data-start=&quot;424&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;551&quot; data-start=&quot;426&quot;&gt;Maryame El Moutamid, lead scientist at &lt;strong data-end=&quot;473&quot; data-start=&quot;465&quot;&gt;SwRI&lt;/strong&gt;, emphasized the significance of the discovery, despite the moon&amp;#39;s small size.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regulate and promote domestic coastal shipping&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Parliament Passes Coastal Shipping Bill to Boost Maritime Trade.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;342&quot; data-start=&quot;276&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;342&quot; data-start=&quot;278&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;303&quot; data-start=&quot;278&quot;&gt;Parliament has passed&lt;/strong&gt; the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;339&quot; data-start=&quot;308&quot;&gt;Coastal Shipping Bill, 2025&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;416&quot; data-start=&quot;343&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;416&quot; data-start=&quot;345&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;360&quot; data-start=&quot;345&quot;&gt;Rajya Sabha&lt;/strong&gt; approved it after it was passed by the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;413&quot; data-start=&quot;400&quot;&gt;Lok Sabha&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;503&quot; data-start=&quot;417&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;503&quot; data-start=&quot;419&quot;&gt;The Bill &lt;strong data-end=&quot;449&quot; data-start=&quot;428&quot;&gt;regulates vessels&lt;/strong&gt; involved in &lt;strong data-end=&quot;479&quot; data-start=&quot;462&quot;&gt;coastal trade&lt;/strong&gt; within Indian waters.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;579&quot; data-start=&quot;504&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;579&quot; data-start=&quot;506&quot;&gt;Aims to &lt;strong data-end=&quot;539&quot; data-start=&quot;514&quot;&gt;consolidate and amend&lt;/strong&gt; laws related to &lt;strong data-end=&quot;576&quot; data-start=&quot;556&quot;&gt;coastal shipping&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;653&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;653&quot; data-start=&quot;582&quot;&gt;Encourages &lt;strong data-end=&quot;619&quot; data-start=&quot;593&quot;&gt;domestic participation&lt;/strong&gt; in the coastal shipping sector.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;750&quot; data-start=&quot;654&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;750&quot; data-start=&quot;656&quot;&gt;Seeks to build a &lt;strong data-end=&quot;704&quot; data-start=&quot;673&quot;&gt;citizen-owned coastal fleet&lt;/strong&gt; for &lt;strong data-end=&quot;730&quot; data-start=&quot;709&quot;&gt;national security&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;747&quot; data-start=&quot;735&quot;&gt;commerce&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;916&quot; data-start=&quot;837&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;916&quot; data-start=&quot;839&quot;&gt;Target: &lt;strong data-end=&quot;876&quot; data-start=&quot;847&quot;&gt;230 million metric tonnes&lt;/strong&gt; of &lt;strong data-end=&quot;913&quot; data-start=&quot;880&quot;&gt;coastal cargo traffic by 2030&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;996&quot; data-start=&quot;917&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;996&quot; data-start=&quot;919&quot;&gt;The Bill aims to &lt;strong data-end=&quot;960&quot; data-start=&quot;936&quot;&gt;minimise regulations&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;993&quot; data-start=&quot;965&quot;&gt;promote ease of business&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1073&quot; data-start=&quot;997&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;1073&quot; data-start=&quot;999&quot;&gt;Will &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1040&quot; data-start=&quot;1004&quot;&gt;strengthen maritime capabilities&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1070&quot; data-start=&quot;1045&quot;&gt;empower coastal areas&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1164&quot; data-start=&quot;1074&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;1164&quot; data-start=&quot;1076&quot;&gt;Coastal shipping currently forms &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1122&quot; data-start=&quot;1109&quot;&gt;only 6&amp;ndash;7%&lt;/strong&gt; of India&amp;rsquo;s &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1161&quot; data-start=&quot;1134&quot;&gt;total logistics traffic&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1248&quot; data-start=&quot;1165&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;1248&quot; data-start=&quot;1167&quot;&gt;Sector has grown: from &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1233&quot; data-start=&quot;1190&quot;&gt;18 million tonnes to 133 million tonnes&lt;/strong&gt; in 10 years.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1334&quot; data-start=&quot;1249&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;1334&quot; data-start=&quot;1251&quot;&gt;Bill supports &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1282&quot; data-start=&quot;1265&quot;&gt;self-reliance&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1301&quot; data-start=&quot;1284&quot;&gt;Make in India&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;1333&quot; data-start=&quot;1307&quot;&gt;eco-friendly transport&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
